Defendant Rickey Donelle Boyd in court with attorney Thomas John Erickson.  Defendant Rickey Donelle Boyd in custody.  Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 20 YEARS CONCURRENT TO 14CF4197, with credit for 422 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank.
Restitution (surcharges appliable) in the amount of $5,986.25 payable to Mary P.
The Court is imposing the applicable fees, restitution, assessments, court costs, and surcharges, including a DNA assessment.  And, you may have to give a swab, which you might be able to have expunged under 165.77.  The Court orders the DOC to collect any monetary amounts ordered today at the rate of max 25% of any amounts provided in secs 973.05(4)(b) and 973.20 while the defendant is in their control.  Any monetary amounts that remain unpaid when the defendant is released from confinement are to be paid as a condition of the extended supervision.  Any monetary mounts that remain unpaid when the sentence is completed are ordered reduced to a judgment against the defendant for the unpaid balance and collection can then proceed under sec. 71.935 as well as other collection procedures.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until hisr civil rights are restored. 
